17/11/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police have busted an international human trafficking ring, detaining six people, the interior ministry announced on Tuesday (November 16th). The group consisted of Macedonians and Afghan citizens allegedly smuggling immigrants from the Middle East and Africa to Western Europe. Police are looking for four other people. The group was charging each potential immigrant between 5,000 and 10,000 euros. (A1, Makfax, Net Press, Sitel - 16/11/10)
